class FloatWithUnits
{
    public float value { get; set; }
    public string unit { get; set; }

    public override string ToString()
    {
        return $"{value} {unit}";
    }
}
```
This method will take the `value` and `unit` fields of the `FloatWithUnits` struct, and concatenate them with a space in between using the `$` operator. The resulting string will be in the format "1.8 meters", where "1.8" is the value and "meters" is the unit.

You can test this method by creating an instance of the `FloatWithUnits` struct and calling the `ToString()` method on it:
```
FloatWithUnits floatWithUnits = new FloatWithUnits { Value = 1.8f, Unit = "meters" };
Console.WriteLine(floatWithUnits); // Output: 1.8 meters
```
